# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types:
#   feat:     A new feature
#   fix:      A bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   style:    Code style changes (formatting, missing semi colons, etc)
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf:     Code change that improves performance
#   test:     Adding or updating tests
#   chore:    Changes to build process or auxiliary tools
#   ci:       Changes to CI/CD configuration
#   build:    Changes to build system or dependencies
#   revert:   Reverts a previous commit
#
# Scope: The area of the codebase affected (e.g., api, auth, runners, workflows)
#
# Subject: Short imperative description (max 50 chars)
#
# Body (optional): Explain what and why, not how (wrap at 72 chars)
#
# Footer (optional): Reference issues, breaking changes
#   Closes #123
#   BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
#
# Examples:
#   feat(runners): add GPU detection and allocation
#   fix(auth): resolve token refresh race condition
#   docs(readme): update installation instructions
#   ci(workflows): optimize Docker build caching
